data.enText: to be greater than a particular number or amount

data.chText: 超越（法律、命令等）的限制
data.enText: to do more than the law or an order, etc. allows you to do
She was exceeding the speed limit (= driving faster than is allowed) .

data.chText: 这些官员超越了他们的权限。
data.enText: The officers had exceeded their authority.

simple_means.memory_skill: ex 出，出去 + ceed 走 → 走出〔固定范围〕→ 超出

means: 超越(法律、命令等)的限制

ex.enText: Tom was exceeding the speed limit.

ex.chText: 工作时间每天不得超过8小时。
ex.enText: Working hours must not exceed 8 hours a day.

synonyms.bx: 指超越职权范围、法律规定等，或超出数量、程度、大小等。

ex.chText: 她在舞蹈方面出类拔萃。

synonyms.bx: 通常指在成就、学识等方面胜过他人，不用进行时。

ex.chText: 中国将在经济上超过日本。
ex.enText: China will surpass Japan in economy.

synonyms.bx: 指在技能、成就等方面超越同类。

tr: be or do something to a greater degree
example: her performance surpasses that of any other student I know
This car outperforms all others in its class

tr: be superior or better than some standard
example: She topped her performance of last year

tr: be greater in scope or size than some standard
example: Their loyalty exceeds their national bonds

value.def: If something exceeds a particular amount or number, it is greater or larger than that amount or number.

example.ex: Its research budget exceeds $700 million a year...
example.tran: 其研究预算每年超过7亿美元。

example.ex: The demand for places at some schools exceeds the supply...
example.tran: 某些学校的入学申请人数超过了招生。
他的表演超出了所有人的期待。

value.tran: 超过，超出（某数量、数字等）

value.def: If you exceed a limit or rule, you go beyond it, even though you are not supposed to or it is against the law.

example.ex: He accepts he was exceeding the speed limit...
I would be exceeding my powers if I ordered the march to be halted.
example.tran: 如果我命令停止游行，我就越权了。
